{
  "texts": [
    "(3) How to achieve good performance under low resource conditions?",
    "Most existing ED methods followed the supervised learning paradigm and relied on a large number of high-quality annotated texts.",
    "When training data is insufficient, their performance becomes suboptimal.",
    "In practical applications, it is very expensive to obtain high-quality annotation data.",
    "Therefore, how to design an efficient ED model that can achieve good performance with only a small amount of annotated texts has become a key challenge.To address all these problems, we propose a novel model named DE3TC, which Detects Events with Effective Event Type Information and Context in an end-to-end way, as shown in Fig. 2."
  ]
}